articles.author: Andrew Osborn, Mark Trevelyan
articles.description: With Alexei Navalny dead and buried in a Moscow graveyard and other anti-Kremlin politicians in exile or jailed, Russia's opposition is at a low ebb. But on Sunday, as Russians go to the polls, opponents of President Vladimir Putin will stage a symbolic protest they hope will resonate.
articles.title: 'Noon against Putin': Opposition urges Russians to fulfil Navalny's 'last wish'
